Reasoning: The paper deals with the algebraic study of transducers and regular languages, which falls under the category of formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). The use of profinite analysis and the study of continuity also suggest a connection to the category of discrete structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the characterization of sequential transducers computable in circuit complexity classes, which relates to the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The study of continuity and its propagation to superclasses may also involve some aspects of logic (cs.LO) and scientific computing (cs.SC).
